## 11/12/2024 -- 20/01/2025: Advanced C#
- **Topics:**
  - **Collection Framework (C# Collections & Generics):**
    - Lists, Dictionaries, HashSets, Queues, Stacks
    - Implementations: List<T>, LinkedList<T>, Dictionary<TKey,TValue>, HashSet<T>
    - Iterators, Lambda Expressions, Delegates, Func & Action
  - **ADO.NET (Equivalent to JDBC):**
    - ADO.NET architecture and providers
    - SQLConnection, SQLCommand, SQLDataReader, SQLDataAdapter
    - Parameters, Stored Procedures, Transactions
    - Executing SQL queries and updates
  - **ASP.NET Core Basics (Equivalent to J2EE):**
    - Overview of .NET & ASP.NET Core architecture
    - Controllers, Routing, Middleware pipeline
    - Razor Pages (JSP equivalent)
    - Application configuration & hosting model
  - **Banking Web Application:**
    - Building a simple banking application with login, transactions, and account management
    - Integrating backend (C#) with frontend (Razor Views)
    - Security considerations (Authentication & Authorization)

## 21/01/2025 -- 04/02/2025: Entity Framework Core (Equivalent to Hibernate)
- **Topics:**
  - **EF Core Configuration:**
    - Setting up DbContext and connection strings
    - Model classes and Fluent API configuration
    - Data annotations and entity mapping (equivalent to hbm.xml)
    - Understanding DbContext, DbSet, and change tracking
  - **CRUD Operations:**
    - Insert, Select, Update, Delete using EF Core
    - LINQ queries (Equivalent to HQL)
    - Query Filters, AsNoTracking, and performance optimization
    - One-to-one, one-to-many, many-to-many relationships
    - Using EF Core migrations to manage schema

## 05/02/2025 -- 03/03/2025: ASP.NET Core MVC & .NET Framework Concepts
- **Topics:**
  - **IoC (Inversion of Control):**
    - Explanation of IoC in ASP.NET Core
    - Built-in Dependency Injection container
    - Service lifetimes: Singleton, Scoped, Transient
  - **DI (Dependency Injection):**
    - Constructor Injection
    - Injecting services into controllers
    - Using interfaces for decoupled architecture
    - Benefits of DI in modular design
  - **Autowiring Equivalent:**
    - Auto-registration patterns
    - AddTransient, AddScoped, AddSingleton
    - Managing multiple implementations
  - **ADO.NET / EF (Combined):**
    - Using EF Core with Repository Pattern
    - Using Dapper for high-performance data access
    - Handling exceptions, pooling, and connection lifecycle
  - **ASP.NET Core MVC:**
    - MVC pattern architecture
    - Controllers, Views, and Models
    - Routing: Attribute & Conventional Routing
    - View engines (Razor), ViewData, ViewBag, TempData
    - Form handling, validation, model binding
    - Working with layout pages & partial views

## 04/03/2025 -- 04/04/2025: ASP.NET Core Web API & Advanced .NET
- **Topics:**
  - **Program.cs & Hosting Model (Equivalent to @SpringBootApplication):**
    - Application startup and middleware configuration
    - Kestrel web server, dependency injection pipeline
    - Configuration via appsettings.json
  - **CLR (Common Language Runtime):**
    - Understanding .NET runtime, assemblies & DLL loading
    - Class loading, garbage collector, JIT compilation
    - Managing dependencies via NuGet packages
  - **DI & Autowiring (Advanced):**
    - Typed HttpClientFactory
    - Options pattern for configuration
    - Logging & middleware-based dependency injection
  - **UI Rendering Technologies (Similar to JSP/Thymeleaf):**
    - Razor Views
    - View Components & Tag Helpers
    - Integrating client-side scripts and frameworks
  - **Database (SQL Server, EF Core, Dapper):**
    - Multiple DbContext setup
    - Connection pools
    - Migrations, Seeding, Relationships
  - **EF Core (Equivalent to Hibernate in Spring Boot):**
    - Lazy vs Eager loading
    - Projection, grouping & joins with LINQ
    - Stored Procedure mapping
    - Optimistic concurrency & tracking behavior
  - **Web API (Equivalent to Spring Boot REST):**
    - Building RESTful endpoints
    - Attribute routing
    - GET, POST, PUT, DELETE operations
    - Model validation & filters
    - Global exception handling
    - Swagger/OpenAPI documentation
  - **Web Services (SOAP & REST):**
    - Creating REST APIs using ASP.NET Core
    - SOAP services with WCF / CoreWCF
    - Consuming SOAP and REST APIs
  - **Microservices:**
    - Introduction to Microservices using .NET
    - API Gateway using Ocelot
    - Service Registry with Consul
    - Resilience & retry patterns with Polly
    - Distributed configuration using Consul/Redis
  - **Security (Equivalent to Spring Security):**
    - Authentication & Authorization middleware
    - Role-based security
    - Securing APIs using JWT
    - OAuth2 & OpenID Connect integration
  - **AOP (Equivalent to Spring AOP):**
    - Action Filters & Exception Filters
    - Custom Middleware for cross-cutting concerns
    - Logging, caching, transactions, auditing
